Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:22.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, yo me voy ya,\N que se está haciendo muy tarde.{Well, I’ll be going now. It’s gotten really late.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.34,0:02:25.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Espera un momento, Araragi!{Hold it right there, Araragi-senpai!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.34,0:02:28.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,Crees que después de que tú,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.04,0:02:32.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,a quien estimo tanto, \Nme haya limpiado la habitación,{Did you think that, after Araragi-senpai, who I hold in the highest esteem, cleans my room for me}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.66,0:02:34.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,iba a dejar que se vaya, ¿sin hacer nada?{I would send him off without doing anything?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.78,0:02:35.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sin hacer nada...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.09,0:02:38.70,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué estás pensando hacerme?{What were you planning on doing to me!?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.68,0:02:43.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pensaba hacer algo de té, pero no,{Pensé que al menos un poco de té, pero mejor no.}{I thought I'd at least make some tea. No, tea won't do.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.30,0:02:47.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,por lo menos debería prepararte la cena.{I should at least prepare a meal for Araragi-senpai.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.36,0:02:50.76,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bien, entonces adelante. {voy a dejar que me hagas la cena.}{All right, then, I'll let you treat me to dinner.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.36,0:02:57.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ahora Araragi, antes de irte a cenar, tómate un baño por favor.{Now then, Araragi-senpai. Before we go for dinner. Please take a bath.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.14,0:03:00.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si cenas después de limpiar, {estando tan sucio,}{if you ate dinner looking that dirty,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.30,0:03:01.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,podría ser un problema.{It would be a bother.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.01,0:03:13.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,No me puedo relajar muy bien aquí... {relajar del todo...} {…I can't relax at all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.30,0:03:17.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡¿Qué pasa aquí?!\N ¡La puerta está cerrada!{What’s this?! The door won’t open! It’s locked!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.89,0:03:21.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Estás bien Araragi? Voy a buscar ayuda.{Are you all right, Araragi-senpai! I’ll come help you out!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.94,0:03:26.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Abrid la puerta inmediatamente! \N¡Salid con las manos en la cabeza, es una orden!{Open this door immediately! Come out with your hands above your head! This is an order!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.00,0:03:28.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,Soy Kanbaru Suruga.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.17,0:03:30.29,HnF,,0,0,0,,Esclava sexual de Araragi.{Araragi-senpai’s sex slave.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:32.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,Mi movimiento especial es el Salto de Paredes.{My special move is the Wall Jump!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.68,0:03:35.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué no se abre...?{Why won’t it open…}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:39.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,No tengo otra opción, voy a buscar esos palos que usan los policías para romper esto.  {I guess I have no choice, I’ll go get those sticks that the riot police use when they break in!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.87,0:03:43.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Estate quieta! ¡Y no vayas a por cosas de las que no sabes ni el nombre!{Stop it! And don't go and bring things you don't know the name of!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.06,0:03:47.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Oh, Araragi, entonces estás bien.{Oh, Araragi-senpai? So you’re safe…}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.26,0:03:53.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,{Esto me ha sorprendido}Menuda sorpresa, pensaba que habías sido capturado, y estaba preocupada. {That really surprised me… I thought Araragi-senpai had been imprisoned, so I was really worried.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.08,0:03:57.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Solamente tú me querrías capturar de esa manera!{¡Solo hay una persona en el mundo que me quisiera capturar, tú!}{There’s only one person in this world that would want to imprison me, and that would be you!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.23,0:04:01.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, a Senjougahara también le gustaría hacerlo.{Not necessarily. Senjougahara-senpai might be likely to do it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.43,0:04:06.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,No creo, ni siquiera ella iría tan lejos.{No way. Not even Senjougahara would go that far.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.11,0:04:11.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,No sé si vas a malinterpretar esto pero, Araragi,{If you’re misunderstanding something then I’d like to correct it, but Araragi-senpai,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:16.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,me puse a lavar tu ropa \Nmientras te estabas bañando,{I just thought I’d wash your clothes for you while you were bathing}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.45,0:04:19.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,sin pensar en nada raro mientras lo hacía.{I had no shameful thoughts whatsoever.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.51,0:04:26.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y si quieres, ¡podría lavarte a ti también!{If you’d like, on top of your clothes, I can wash your body for you, too!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.14,0:04:27.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por delante y por detrás.{From the front and the back!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.23,0:04:31.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como agradecimiento por limpiar mi habitación.{As thanks for making my room nice and clean.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.46,0:04:35.19,HnF,,0,0,0,,Estoy diciendo que me gustaría limpiarte a ti también.{I’m saying I’d like to make your body nice and clean, Araragi-senpai!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.19,0:04:37.67,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Primero limpia tu mente!{Clean up your own mind first!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.28,0:04:42.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,A pesar de que te tomas un buen baño todos los días, sigues teniendo una mente sucia.{Even though you use such a nice bath every day, you have such a dirty mind!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.72,0:04:48.60,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cuando dices que es un buen baño,\N realmente es cierto. {When you say that it is a nice bath, I cannot help but say that it is so.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:52.67,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque sea mi propio baño, es verdad que es bueno.{Si actúo humildemente aquí, podría parecer sarcástica.}{If I act humbly here, it might seem sarcastic.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.67,0:04:59.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero no es solo el baño, el agua es buena también. Porque viene del pozo de nuestro patio.{But it’s not just the bath; the water is nice, too. \N We boil the water drawn from the well in our yard.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:04:59.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(488,215)\b1}Este agua tiene de algún modo, un montón de cosas {\b0\c&HFFFFFF&}{It’s deep somethingwater with lots of somethingsium}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.69,0:05:02.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hablando de eso, Araragi.{Speaking of which, Araragi-senpai.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.52,0:05:04.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué pasa, Kanbaru?{What is it, Kanbaru-kouhai?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:07.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,El agua del pozo tiene un bonito pasado, ¿sabías?{That well water actually has a past, you know?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.92,0:05:09.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿De qué tipo de pasado estás hablando?{What kind of a past are you talking about?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.52,0:05:12.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sobre una historia sobre mi padre.{It’s a story about my father, you see.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.87,0:05:17.85,HnF,,0,0,0,,Naturalmente, mi padre también utilizaba este baño con regularidad.{Naturally, my father also used this bath on a regular basis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.08,0:05:21.35,HnF,,0,0,0,,Con regularidad, ¿eh?{On a regular basis, huh?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:25.63,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sin embargo, siendo joven\N cuando se tomaba un baño, {However, when he was young, when he took a bath, on extremely rare occasions,}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.63,0:05:27.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,en extrañas ocasiones, algo misterioso pasaba.{there was something very curious that would happen.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.45,0:05:28.77,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Algo misterioso?{Something curious?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.20,0:05:32.70,HnF,,0,0,0,,Un fenómeno misterioso, podríamos decir.{A curious phenomenon, I guess you could call it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.70,0:05:37.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,No creo que fuera algo relacionado con las excentricidades, pero era un fenómeno extraño.{It might not go as far as oddity-related, but there was this mysterious phenomenon.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.78,0:05:41.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,No entiendo de qué estás hablando.{No se te da muy bien contar los detalles.}{You're being awfully, or should I say considerably, specific with details.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.88,0:05:45.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,Araragi, mira la superficie del agua de esa bañera.{Araragi-senpai. Please look at the surface of the water in that bathtub.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.42,0:05:53.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Estoy mirando, pero... ¿Qué pasa con el agua?{I’m looking at it. It might be too late now… But is there something about this water?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.86,0:05:59.62,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, no me refería a eso. No es el agua a lo que dije que miraras.{No, no, I don’t mean that. I said it clearly, didn’t I? It’s not the water I wanted you to look at}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.44,0:06:01.25,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sino a la superficie del agua.{It’s the surface.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.53,0:06:05.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(346,197)}Desde: Senjougahara Hitagi
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.53,0:06:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(486,340)}Asunto: Al parecer has ido a la habitación de Kanbaru.{So apparently you went to Kanbaru's room. }
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.53,0:06:05.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(247,484)}Texto: (Vacío) {(Empty)}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.38,0:06:07.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Muere.{Die.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.38,0:06:10.27,HnF,,0,0,0,,Muere, muere, muere, muere, muere, muere, muere.{Die. Die. Die. Die. Die. Die. Die.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.78,0:06:13.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,P-Pero aún no puedo morir.{I-I can't die just yet.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.36,0:06:16.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,Porque acabo de empezar a salir contigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.65,0:06:19.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Porque apenas hemos empezado nuestra relación.{We’ve only just started going out.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.19,0:06:25.71,HnF,,0,0,0,,Porque quiero tener más citas contigo. ¡La vida es demasiado preciosa como para morir justo ahora!{I want to go on more dates with you. Life is way too precious to die right now!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:30.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,Oh, vaya. Dices cosas muy bonitas. \NEn ese caso no tienes por qué morir.{Oh my. You’re saying some really pleasant things, aren’t you. Then, you don’t have to die.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.78,0:06:32.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,Senjougahara, eres muy fácil.{Senjougahara-san, you’re too easy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.78,0:06:34.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tenías que haberme dicho que muera un poco más{Se supone que me tienes que decir que me muera un poco más.}{You're supposed to tell me to die a little more than that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.53,0:06:38.43,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y por eso fui hoy a la casa de Kanbaru.{And so that's why I went to Kanbaru’s house today to clean.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.10,0:06:43.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ir, y limpiar la habitación de una menor, parece que cuidas bien de ella.{To go and clean the room of an underclassman, aren't you the caring role model.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.74,0:06:47.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque ya tomarte un baño, me parece descarado. \N{Aunque ir y tomarte un baño allí, es impresentable.} Pienso que deberías morir.{Although going and taking a bath there is rather impudent. I think you should die.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:48.93,HnF,,0,0,0,,No lo pienses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.93,0:06:51.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No crees que es mejor eso, \N a que diga que te voy a matar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.82,0:06:58.03,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, ¿que piensas de la historia de Kanbaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.03,0:07:00.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, es cierto que es una historia extraña.{Well, it sure was a mysterious story.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.74,0:07:07.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, no es extraña. Creo que sería más como "romántica".{No, maybe it wasn’t mysterious? I don’t know if I should say it was a romantic story.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.22,0:07:11.03,HnF,,0,0,0,,El padre de Kanbaru vio la imagen de su futura esposa,{In the surface of the water, Kanbaru’s dad}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.03,0:07:12.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,en la superficie del agua.{vio la imagen de la chica que estaría junto a él en el futuro.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.64,0:07:14.94,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Esa es la historia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:18.37,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,No siempre, solo algunas veces.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:23.75,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Aparentemente, vio la imagen de su esposa\N en la superficie del agua.{Apparently he saw the image of the partner he would elope with in the surface of the water,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:27.89,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Pero tiempo después, dejó de aparecer.{But after a while it stopped appearing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.89,0:07:33.47,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Justo cuando justo cuando la conoció a ella, a Gaen Tooe.{So when Kanbaru’s dad met Kanbaru’s mom, that is, Gaen Tooe,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.47,0:07:35.21,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Estuvo muy sorprendido.{he was extremely shocked.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.02,0:07:39.67,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por cierto, cuando Kanbaru te dijo que mirases la superficie del agua,{Incidentally, when you looked at the surface of the water when Kanbaru told you to.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.67,0:07:42.37,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿A quién viste ahí?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.74,0:07:43.73,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿A mí?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.73,0:07:44.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿A mí?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.68,0:07:46.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿O tal vez a mí?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.22,0:07:47.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,{¡Qué molestia!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.10,0:07:48.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿A Hanekawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.23,0:07:49.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Kanbaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.28,0:07:50.25,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Hachikuji?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:51.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,{¡Espeluznante!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.30,0:07:54.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Realmente no había nadie en el reflejo.{No había nadie reflejado allí en realidad...}{No, there wasn’t anybody reflected there…}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:57.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Solo estaba el mío propio, naturalmente.{It was just my own reflection, like normal.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.56,0:08:04.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, ya me lo había dicho Kanbaru.{Well, I’ve heard from Kanbaru about it before, you see.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.07,0:08:07.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque también es verdad que lo había olvidado hasta ahora.{Well, the truth was that I had forgotten until you told me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.53,0:08:13.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cuando me lo contó, aún era una buena chica,\N y no le dije nada extraño.{Back then I was a good kid and didn’t say anything unrefined.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:19.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como acabo de decir, tenía una buena personalidad en ese momento...{Like I said, since my personality was good at the time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.69,0:08:24.73,HnF,,0,0,0,,No era la cabeza dura, ingrata y caprichosa que soy ahora.{Back before I was a contrarian, ill-natured, awful-tempered girl. ESTO ESTÁ MAL TRADUCIDO!!! D=!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.57,0:08:27.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso es un pelín demasiada auto-consciencia.{That’s a little too much self-awareness.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.17,0:08:29.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,Nunca comenté esa historia romántica{I didn’t unrefinedly include interpretations}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:34.37,HnF,,0,0,0,,porque la explicación ni siquiera era la de una historia sobrenatural.{to that romantic love story that didn’t even amount to an oddity story, is what I meant.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.95,0:08:38.48,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y ahora el epílogo, o mejor, la conclusión.{And now for the epilogue; or rather, the punch line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.11,0:08:40.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eh, ¿cómo?{Eh? What?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:45.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Estás diciendo que el padre de Kanbaru tan solo vio su propio reflejo? {So, are you saying that Kanbaru’s dad just saw his own face in the surface of the water like a mirror.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.00,0:08:48.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Y pensó que era su propia alma gemela?{And thought it was his ‘fated partner’?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.26,0:08:53.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, no creo que sea eso.{No, I don’t think… that could happen.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.69,0:08:58.77,HnF,,0,0,0,,La superficie del agua se puede agitar y desdibujar, no es tan buena como un espejo.{The water’s surface can shake and glisten and blur, it’s not as good as a mirror.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.10,0:09:04.32,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No crees que pudo haber confundido ese reflejo borroso suyo con el de una chica?{And isn’t it possible that he might have seen that blurred reflection of his as a girl?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.92,0:09:07.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, supongo que es posible mientras era pequeño,{Well… I guess it’s true that, since a young child}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.80,0:09:11.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,durante esa edad no hay mucha diferencia entre sexos, tendría sentido.{lacks much in the way of gender differentation, that story might be possible.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.06,0:09:13.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero una vez que crece,{But once he became an adult,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.20,0:09:17.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,o con un poco de sentido común, normalmente se daría cuenta.{or even just got something of a sense of judgment, he’d normally notice}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.94,0:09:22.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y se dio cuenta. Por eso dejó de aparecer.{He did notice. That’s why it stopped appearing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.94,0:09:26.79,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sin embargo, se quedó con el recuerdo de haber visto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:29.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,lo que parecía una chica\N sobre la superficie del agua.{However, he was left with the memory that he saw what looked like a person in the surface of the water.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:34.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Y por eso pensó que era su alma gemela? Algo falla ahí.{Hay un gran salto para esa conclusión.}{And so that's why he thought it was his 'fated partner’? That’s quite the conclusion to jump to.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:36.55,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es porque lo has entendido mal.{Eso es porque el orden está cambiado.}{That's because you've got the order backwards.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.55,0:09:40.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,Fue el hecho de conocer a su "alma gemela",{It was after he met someone he thought to be his 'fated partner,’}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.05,0:09:44.58,HnF,,0,0,0,,lo que le recordó al reflejo que vio hace tiempo.{that she resembled his own reflection that he'd seen in the water long ago.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.82,0:09:49.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Así que eso pensó él?{, así se tomaría desde su punto de vista?}{Oh, so that's how it goes from his point of view.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.78,0:09:53.76,HnF,,0,0,0,,En el amor, se tiende a buscar a alguien que se parece a ti.{In romance, you tend to end up looking for someone who resembles you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.53,0:09:56.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque esto es solo mi opinión.{Well, this is just an interpretation of mine.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.28,0:10:01.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si le dices algo a Kanbaru, te mataré.{If you say too much to Kanbaru, I’ll kill you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.25,0:10:03.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si se lo cuentas, no te perdonaré.{If you do tell her, I won’t forgive you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:07.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si se te escapa algo por accidente, por favor, suicídate antes de mañana.{If you let something slip on accident, please kill yourself by tomorrow.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.06,0:10:17.64,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hola Kanbaru, hay algo que se me olvidó preguntar, ¿qué hay de ti?{Hey, Kanbaru. There was something I forgot to ask you, but what about you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.64,0:10:22.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué ves cuando miras la superficie del agua del baño?{What do you see when you look at the surface of the water in that bath?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.43,0:10:27.35,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Si la explicación de su padre es correcta,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.35,0:10:31.46,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,entonces debería aparecer la pareja de Kanbaru.{If Kanbaru’s dad’s explanation was correct, then Kanbaru’s fated partner would show up.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.30,0:10:36.40,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Pero si la explicación de Senjougahara es cierta,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.40,0:10:41.58,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,probablemente viese un reflejo que se confundiría con el de su madre.{then the image that might be reflected could be Kanbaru's mom.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.38,0:10:45.55,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,No sería extraño tampoco que viese el reflejo de su padre.{It wouldn’t be strange if Kanbaru saw her dad’s reflection instead.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.48,0:10:48.99,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y si ese fuese el caso, sería muy romántico a su manera.{If that was the case then that would be pretty romantic in its own right.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:54.03,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Mm? Ah, puedo ver mis pechos por supuesto.{Hm? Oh. I can see my own breasts of course.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.03,0:10:58.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,Modestia aparte, son muy eróticos, y me quedo viéndolos todo el rato mientras me baño.{If I do say so myself, they’re very erotic, and I stare at them all the time when I’m bathing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.86,0:11:05.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,La diferencia con mi vientre es bastante, y todas las noches siento mi corazón palpitar cuando los veo.{The contrast with my abs below them is really vivid, and every night I feel a rush of blood when I look at them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.05,0:11:07.61,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sinceramente, nada más cabe en mi campo de visión.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:09.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué preguntas, Arara-?
